WEBVTT

00:00:15.940 --> 00:00:17.420
To understand a balance sheet

00:00:17.420 --> 00:00:20.460
well we have to know the first thing

00:00:20.460 --> 00:00:21.720
that on the right side we have

00:00:21.720 --> 00:00:23.720
the origins of financing, that

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:25.380
is, it informs us of where the

00:00:25.380 --> 00:00:26.820
funds come from.

00:00:26.980 --> 00:00:28.900
On the left side we have the other

00:00:28.900 --> 00:00:30.380
perspective that is where we have

00:00:30.380 --> 00:00:32.600
invested those funds, which

00:00:32.680 --> 00:00:33.380
are the assets.

00:00:34.420 --> 00:00:36.320
We go with the right side, with

00:00:36.320 --> 00:00:37.400
the sources of funding.

00:00:37.400 --> 00:00:39.440
Here we have three large masses.

00:00:39.600 --> 00:00:40.920
Current liabilities

00:00:40.920 --> 00:00:44.260
are debts that have a

00:00:44.260 --> 00:00:45.580
maturity of less than

00:00:45.580 --> 00:00:46.940
one year.

00:00:47.480 --> 00:00:49.560
We have non-current liabilities,

00:00:50.020 --> 00:00:51.960
which are debts with a maturity

00:00:51.960 --> 00:00:53.940
greater than the year, and

00:00:53.940 --> 00:00:55.740
we also have our own funds.

00:00:56.160 --> 00:00:57.980
Permanent resources

00:00:57.980 --> 00:01:00.260
are called the own funds

00:01:00.260 --> 00:01:02.080
and non-current liabilities.

00:01:02.080 --> 00:01:02.940


00:01:05.030 --> 00:01:06.490
On the asset side, what is it that

00:01:06.490 --> 00:01:06.930
we have?

00:01:07.210 --> 00:01:08.270
We have assets that are more

00:01:08.270 --> 00:01:11.090
liquid, called current assets.

00:01:11.790 --> 00:01:13.470
The criterion here is that they

00:01:13.470 --> 00:01:14.990
are assets that will be converted

00:01:14.990 --> 00:01:16.750
in principle into treasury in

00:01:16.750 --> 00:01:17.850
less than a year.

00:01:19.130 --> 00:01:20.870
They are usually the most

00:01:20.870 --> 00:01:22.230
operational assets, related to

00:01:22.230 --> 00:01:23.310
the company’s own activity.

00:01:23.830 --> 00:01:25.310
And then you have the assets that

00:01:25.310 --> 00:01:27.390
are not liquid, which are called

00:01:27.390 --> 00:01:28.670
non-current, but good that they are

00:01:28.670 --> 00:01:31.570
the immovilized, the fixed assets, etc.

00:01:31.610 --> 00:01:33.790
As you can see, we have classified all

00:01:33.790 --> 00:01:39.270
of the assets and their requirements.

00:01:39.330 --> 00:01:40.250
Basically, we have two

00:01:40.250 --> 00:01:40.790
large blocks.

00:01:42.610 --> 00:01:44.230
Permanent assets and non-current

00:01:44.230 --> 00:01:47.650
assets, say they have a longer

00:01:47.650 --> 00:01:49.510
term, and current assets

00:01:49.510 --> 00:01:51.430
and non-current liabilities,

00:01:51.430 --> 00:01:54.030
which are more liquid

00:01:54.030 --> 00:01:56.010
or are debts that have a higher

00:01:56.010 --> 00:01:58.270
demand, that is, that will

00:01:58.310 --> 00:01:59.930
expire in the next year.

00:02:03.910 --> 00:02:05.030
When we talk about the structure

00:02:05.030 --> 00:02:06.750
of capital, we are talking about

00:02:06.750 --> 00:02:10.830
the proportion of foreign funds

00:02:10.830 --> 00:02:12.090
and own funds, that is, how we have

00:02:12.090 --> 00:02:13.230
funded ourselves.

00:02:13.590 --> 00:02:14.850
This can be seen in the balance sheet.

00:02:15.430 --> 00:02:17.010
As we have seen before, on the right

00:02:17.010 --> 00:02:18.830
side we have the origins or

00:02:18.830 --> 00:02:20.290
sources of funding.

00:02:21.690 --> 00:02:23.230
And here what is we have to understand?

00:02:23.930 --> 00:02:25.030
Well, we have to understand that

00:02:25.030 --> 00:02:26.410
the liabilities or foreign

00:02:26.410 --> 00:02:29.290
funds have a risk, because you

00:02:29.290 --> 00:02:30.690
have to return them, and if you

00:02:30.690 --> 00:02:32.970
can’t return it you’ll go bankrupt.

00:02:33.130 --> 00:02:34.390
They have a risk and have a

00:02:34.390 --> 00:02:36.590
cost, because you have to pay interest.

00:02:37.150 --> 00:02:39.510
In the case of own funds, it is not

00:02:39.730 --> 00:02:41.790
so, because they do not pose any

00:02:41.790 --> 00:02:43.030
risk to the company.

00:02:44.190 --> 00:02:45.430
The risk is assumed by the partners,

00:02:45.430 --> 00:02:46.730
who invest their money and take

00:02:46.730 --> 00:02:50.250
the risk of not recovering it

00:02:50.250 --> 00:02:51.770
or not getting the profitability

00:02:51.770 --> 00:02:52.910
they expect, etc.

00:02:54.430 --> 00:02:56.170
In addition, own funds do not have

00:02:56.170 --> 00:02:57.770
direct cost to the company,

00:02:57.770 --> 00:03:00.490
because you do not have the contractual

00:03:00.490 --> 00:03:02.150
obligation to remunerate

00:03:02.150 --> 00:03:03.590
the partners.

00:03:03.730 --> 00:03:05.730
If so, dividends are paid,

00:03:05.730 --> 00:03:08.390
but they are not like interest.

00:03:08.530 --> 00:03:10.390
Well, the ratio between one and

00:03:10.390 --> 00:03:12.250
the other is what is called the

00:03:12.250 --> 00:03:13.630
leverage ratio or the indebtedness

00:03:13.630 --> 00:03:15.490
ratio, which is something you

00:03:15.490 --> 00:03:16.290
have to be very familiar

00:03:16.290 --> 00:03:17.570
with, because it has a

00:03:17.690 --> 00:03:21.350
huge impact on the company’

00:03:21.350 --> 00:03:23.310
s risk, valuation, profitability,

00:03:23.310 --> 00:03:24.490
etc.

00:03:25.070 --> 00:03:27.230
We will see it later.

