We should understand what kind of

00:03:33.840 --> 00:03:35.660
financing we should resort to depending

00:03:35.660 --> 00:03:37.560
on the assets of a company.

00:03:38.500 --> 00:03:39.580
That is, it is that of course, it

00:03:39.580 --> 00:03:40.680
has nothing to do with having

00:03:40.680 --> 00:03:42.460
a company in which assets, for example,

00:03:42.460 --> 00:03:44.080
are very liquid.

00:03:45.000 --> 00:03:46.860
Imagine there are stocks in which

00:03:46.860 --> 00:03:48.840
you have a company in which, almost

00:03:48.840 --> 00:03:50.560
if your assets are, for example,

00:03:50.560 --> 00:03:52.920
immovated, non-current assets.

00:03:53.360 --> 00:03:55.800
Well, it is very easy to understand this.

00:03:56.420 --> 00:03:58.460
If we have assets, how do we finance

00:03:58.460 --> 00:03:59.900
assets that are not current,

00:03:59.900 --> 00:04:01.520
that are not liquid, that

00:04:01.520 --> 00:04:02.500
will not be converted

00:04:02.500 --> 00:04:03.440
into treasury.

