into treasury that will allow

00:04:19.540 --> 00:04:22.280
you to repay those debts.

00:04:22.400 --> 00:04:23.900
Stay with this concept.

00:04:24.080 --> 00:04:25.080
With current assets,

00:04:25.080 --> 00:04:26.520
we could do a similar

00:04:26.520 --> 00:04:27.340
analysis.

00:04:27.620 --> 00:04:29.640
If current assets are liquid and

00:04:29.640 --> 00:04:34.500
will be converted into treasury,

00:04:34.500 --> 00:04:35.720
we could finance them

00:04:35.720 --> 00:04:38.960
with short-term liabilities,

00:04:38.960 --> 00:04:39.320
right?

00:04:40.180 --> 00:04:41.600
They will be able to make

00:04:41.600 --> 00:04:44.100
money to repay those debts.

00:04:44.280 --> 00:04:46.120
But in this analysis, there

00:04:46.120 --> 00:04:47.540
are other factors that need

00:04:47.540 --> 00:04:48.860
to be included, right?

00:04:48.860 --> 00:04:49.660
What are the operational

00:04:49.660 --> 00:04:51.200
funding needs we will see.

00:04:56.080 --> 00:04:57.140
We need to look at the

00:04:57.140 --> 00:05:00.840
funding needs of

00:05:00.840 --> 00:05:01.660
a company.

00:05:02.120 --> 00:05:03.440
So how much do we have to finance?

00:05:03.820 --> 00:05:04.840
Well, let’s start with the

00:05:04.840 --> 00:05:05.780
asset, because what you have to

00:05:05.780 --> 00:05:06.960
finance is the asset.

00:05:07.100 --> 00:05:09.300
We have a non-current asset,

00:05:09.580 --> 00:05:12.400
which is fixed, immovilized assets.

00:05:12.560 --> 00:05:14.820
We also need to add current

00:05:14.820 --> 00:05:16.860
assets.

00:05:16.940 --> 00:05:18.200
And in this case we will think only of

00:05:18.200 --> 00:05:19.500
the operative ones, which are

00:05:19.500 --> 00:05:20.940
necessary for the activity.

00:05:21.360 --> 00:05:22.160
Let us put, for example,

00:05:22.160 --> 00:05:23.580
stocks and customers.

00:05:23.980 --> 00:05:24.720
Well, that’s all we

00:05:24.720 --> 00:05:25.860
should finance, right?

00:05:27.260 --> 00:05:28.280
Well, here you have to consider

00:05:28.280 --> 00:05:29.640
a very important concept, which

00:05:29.680 --> 00:05:31.700
is spontaneous financing, which

00:05:32.180 --> 00:05:33.420
are the providers.

00:05:33.820 --> 00:05:35.900
Because suppliers help us to

00:05:35.900 --> 00:05:38.840
finance part of our activity.

00:05:39.100 --> 00:05:41.400
You think, imagine you have a trade

00:05:41.400 --> 00:05:42.300
where you don’t have fixed

00:05:42.300 --> 00:05:43.280
assets.

00:05:43.420 --> 00:05:44.700
You only have to fund the

00:05:44.700 --> 00:05:45.820
stocks, the purchases.

00:05:46.860 --> 00:05:48.600
You do not have any other assets.

00:05:49.500 --> 00:05:51.140
You sell at the expense,

00:05:51.140 --> 00:05:52.660
but pay your suppliers

00:05:52.660 --> 00:05:54.020
90 days.

00:05:54.400 --> 00:05:55.820
Well, it’s that your suppliers,

00:05:55.820 --> 00:05:57.160
in this case, are helping you

00:05:57.160 --> 00:05:58.940
to finance your entire activity.

00:05:59.380 --> 00:06:00.700
You do not have to put money

00:06:00.700 --> 00:06:01.540
in advance.

00:06:01.780 --> 00:06:03.720
You sell at the counter and pay the

00:06:03.720 --> 00:06:06.320
supplier 90 days.

00:06:06.340 --> 00:06:08.760
Well, from this, what we calculate

00:06:08.760 --> 00:06:10.440
are operational fund needs

00:06:10.440 --> 00:06:12.040
or working capital, which

00:06:12.040 --> 00:06:13.760
are absolutely basic

00:06:13.760 --> 00:06:16.060
concepts in finance.

00:06:16.220 --> 00:06:16.940
How is it calculated?

00:06:17.000 --> 00:06:18.480
Well, because we have current

00:06:18.480 --> 00:06:21.700
assets less current operating

00:06:21.700 --> 00:06:23.120
liabilities, less suppliers,

00:06:23.120 --> 00:06:24.400
basically.

00:06:25.740 --> 00:06:28.060
The NOF is the amount

00:06:28.060 --> 00:06:29.320
we really have to finance, because

00:06:29.360 --> 00:06:30.960
the rest helps us to

00:06:30.960 --> 00:06:32.080
finance suppliers.

00:06:33.840 --> 00:06:35.640
So, let’s think about what is

00:06:35.640 --> 00:06:37.060
the total amount that a company

00:06:37.060 --> 00:06:37.840
has to finance?

00:06:38.440 --> 00:06:39.540
The total financial needs

00:06:39.540 --> 00:06:41.240
we have here in red.

00:06:41.300 --> 00:06:42.900
Well, because it is the non-current

00:06:42.900 --> 00:06:45.720
assets plus the operational

00:06:45.720 --> 00:06:47.720
needs of funds.

00:06:47.860 --> 00:06:50.100
So the later you pay your suppliers,

00:06:50.100 --> 00:06:51.560
the higher the balance of suppliers,

00:06:51.560 --> 00:06:53.440
the better because our overall

00:06:53.440 --> 00:06:54.640
financial needs will

00:06:54.640 --> 00:06:56.600
be better, they will

00:06:57.140 --> 00:06:58.320
be lower.

